  <Docs>
    <summary>Provides a mechanism by which a <see cref="T:System.Activities.Location" /> can be resolved at runtime.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 <xref:System.Activities.Variable>, <xref:System.Activities.RuntimeArgument>, and <xref:System.Activities.DelegateArgument> are all <xref:System.Activities.LocationReference>s. The runtime manages state in an environment associated with each <xref:System.Activities.ActivityInstance>. A <xref:System.Activities.Location> is a read/write proxy to a value stored in this environment. A <xref:System.Activities.LocationReference> provides a mechanism by which a <xref:System.Activities.Location> can be resolved at runtime.  
  
 This is an abstract class.  
  
 ]]></format>
    </remarks>
  </Docs>
